  "original_title": "\u0b8a\u0b9f\u0b95\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb2\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bb2\u0b9a\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bca\u0bb2\u0bc8 \u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0baa\u0bca\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0bb8\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bcb\u0ba4\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb7\u0bbe\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0b9f\u0bbf \u0b9a\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0bc7\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bcb\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf \u0b8a\u0b9f\u0b95\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb2\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bbe\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1 \u0bb5\u0bc6\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f \u0ba4\u0b95\u0bb5\u0bb2\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Information released by the Organization to Protect Journalists quoting Police Inspector Nishanta de Silva on the killing of journalist Lasanda.",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to the International Organization for the Protection of Journalists, the former officer of the Intelligence Division, Inspector General of Police Nishantha de Silva has found that the murder of journalist Lasanda Wickramatunga in 2009 and the current president are closely related to the assassination of journalist Lasanda Wickramatunga in 2009.",
        "Police Inspector Nishantha de Silva was conducting extensive investigations into the assassination of journalist Lasanda Wickramatunga between 2015 and 2019, but was forced to flee the country after Gotabaya Rajapaksa was elected president in November 2019.",
        "After that, when the murder of journalist Lasantha Wickramatunga was taken up for investigation in the People's Tribunal related to the assassination of journalists established in The Hague, Netherlands on the 13th of May, Nishantha de Silva, who was present in Athirpayam, testified about the things he found regarding the assassination of Lasantha.",
        "This is the first time that Nishanta de Silva has appeared in front of a public institution since leaving the country and has publicly commented on evidence related to Lasanda's murder.",
        "Although President Gotabaya Rajapaksa has denied the allegations leveled against him regarding illegal killings, abductions and forced disappearances, Chief Police Inspector Nishantha de Silva, who served as the investigating officer of many important cases including the murder of journalist Lasantha Wickramatunga, the kidnapping and torture of Keeth Noyar, and the kidnapping and torture of Bothala Jayantha, left the country after Lasantha left the country. The International Organization for the Protection of Journalists has said that his comments related to the massacre have caused shockwaves."
      ],
